Trendforce Global smartphone production volume for 1Q19 totaled 311M units showing a YoY decrease of 9 The outlook for 2Q19 indicates that smartphone demand will stabilize and the traditional busy season for stockup activities will arrive in the latter half of 2Q19 Thus the global smartphone production volume in 2Q19 is forecasted to register no significant YoY change over 2018 holding steady at the level of 350M units TrendForce further forecasts that the global production volume in 2019 will contract by 37 from 2018 to around 14B unitsChina previously one of the main battlegrounds for Apples highend phones saw Apple sales 1Q19 plummet by 26 YoY to 415M units due to the double whammy of the USChina trade dispute and the increasing competition from Huaweis highend smartphonesTrendForce forecasts that the total AAPL iPhone production volume for 2Q19 will still register a drop from the previous quarter to around 40M units
